oubliette (0.4.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Categories are now explicit. `obl add` no longer creates a category on
    demand; it errors if the category does not exist (breaking change for
    anyone relying on `obl add -c <new-category>` to create one).
  * Add `obl cat add <name>` and `obl cat rm <name>` to manage categories.
    `cat add` appends at the next priority prefix; `cat rm` removes an empty
    category and compacts the remaining priorities so the numbering stays
    contiguous. Removing a non-empty category is refused.
  * Default categories are now seeded only when the store is first created, so
    removing a category is no longer undone by the next `obl add`.

 -- Stephen Gemin <s.gemin88@gmail.com>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

oubliette (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add `obl export [output-base]` command to archive all notes to a single
    portable file. Tries tar.gz, zip, and plain tar in order, using the first
    available tool. Cleans up partial output on failure before trying the next
    format. Appends the appropriate extension to the output base; defaults to
    oubliette-YYYY-MM-DD.{tar.gz,zip,tar} in the current directory.

 -- Stephen Gemin <s.gemin88@gmail.com>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

oubliette (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Renamed project from lnotes to oubliette; binary renamed from `notes` to `obl`.
  * Environment variable renamed: LNOTES_DIR → OBL_DIR.
  * Storage directory renamed: ~/Documents/lnotes → ~/Documents/oubliette
    (breaking change for anyone with existing notes — move them manually).

 -- Stephen Gemin <s.gemin88@gmail.com>  Tue, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

lnotes (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release: notes add, notes rm, notes ls, notes search subcommands
  * Notes stored as Markdown files with YAML frontmatter under ~/Documents/lnotes;
    XDG_DOCUMENTS_DIR respected on Linux
  * Five default categories with numeric prefixes (01_general through 05_medical)
  * New categories created automatically with the next available prefix
  * Search uses POSIX ERE matched case-insensitively; supports title-only (-t)
    and body-only (-b) modes
  * Pure Makefile build system, C99, GCC and Clang supported; -Wall -Wextra
    -Wpedantic -Werror enforced
  * GitHub Actions CI: Linux/macOS matrix, AddressSanitizer + UBSan, cppcheck
    static analysis, valgrind memory check; 10-minute timeout per job

 -- Stephen Gemin <s.gemin88@gmail.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 22:26:26 +0000
